    <text type="letter">
        <body>
            
            <pb xml:id="leaf001r" facs="nar.02986.001.jpg" type="recto"/>
            
            <ab>March 27, 1871.</ab>
            <ab>Hon. Hamilton Fish,</ab>
            <ab>Secretary of State.</ab>
            <ab>Sir:</ab>
            <ab>In pursuance of your wishes and those of the Secretary of the Treasury, I directed the District Attorney of the Eastern District of Michigan to release
            
             <note type="authorial" place="left" rend="none">the two Michigan vessels released.</note>
                
            <pb xml:id="leaf001v" facs="nar.02986.002.jpg" type="verso"/>
                
            two vessels seized for violation of the revenue laws, and also to discontinue all proceedings against Mr. Little, the owner.</ab>
            <ab>I enclose a copy of the letter from the District Attorney, from which it appears that these directions have been complied with.</ab>
            <ab>Very respectfully, &amp;c.</ab>
            <ab>A. T. Akerman,</ab>
            <ab>Attorney General.</ab>              
                
        </body>
